{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a3444836-6c0b-417d-bdce-d58f1ca731e2","content":"Here's how to migrate:\n\n**1. Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with the MTP runner:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.mtp\" Version=\"1.0.0\" />\n```\n\nKeep your `xunit` (or `xunit.v3`) package as-is.\n\n**2. Enable MTP** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (MTP makes test projects self-contained apps).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `xunit.runner.mtp` v1.x targets xUnit v2 (`xunit` 2.x). It's the drop-in MTP replacement for `xunit.runner.visualstudio`.\n- If you later upgrade to xUnit v3, the MTP runner is built-in — you won't need either runner package.\n- Some VSTest-specific `.runsettings` options may need adjustment. MTP uses `--` CLI args instead (e.g., `dotnet test -- --help` to see options).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5cc08750-dfac-4bd5-bd36-3e17f307c294","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide concise guidance.","outputTokens":403,"requestId":"CFCC:1CA5E9:5E01989:6938394:69EC0DF2"},"id":"9527da3b-10bf-4b17-907c-5792c91188ae","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:42:35.760Z","parentId":"137f786c-3267-4900-b17b-70922b2f164e"}
